CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1953, page 6, reads: "Omegas Host District Representative - Iota Chapter of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity played host to the Second District representative, Herschel (rip) Day, at a buffet dinder [dinner] held at the Loendi Club on Sunday, April 12. Left to right: Eugene Morris, James Bell, Basileus of Omicron Psi Chapter; Samuel Johnson, Clevester Powell, Wendell Allen, Paul Saunders, George Bell and James Garnett. Second row: J.D. Lewis, William G. Nunn Sr., Albert Brown, Ford, Carl Redwood, Day, Charles B. Watkins, Sessions and Frank Lavelle. Third row: Mr. Page Mansfield Cole, George Harley, Harry Conrad, Frank A. Nelson Jr., Everett Utterback and Roland Sawyer. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity members, front row from left: Eugene Morris, James Bell, Samuel Johnson, Clevester Powell, Wendell Allen, Paul Saunders, George Bell, James Garnett; second row: J. D. Lewis, William G. Nunn Sr., Albert Brown, Ford, Carl Redwood, Herschel "Rip" Day, Charles B. Watkins, Sessions, Frank Lavelle; third row: Page Mansfield Cole, George Harley, Harry Conrad, Frank A. Nelson Jr., Everett Utterback Sr., and Roland Sawyer, gathered for the Iota Chapter of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity dinner at the Loendi Club
